{
  "type": "modeling_module",
  "steps": [

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "In this next module, the modeling phase, I am going to demonstrate what an interaction with the learner would look like from presenting the SD, awaiting response, and providing reinforcement or error correction."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "We will demonstrate independent responding, including reinforcement and error correction across various SDs and talk through them as we go."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "As we progress through these interactions, I will ask you questions to determine your level of understanding and you will be given the option to replay interactions after they are completed, or ask for me to continue as we did previously. Shall I continue or repeat?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [{
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 0.5,
          "duration": 1.5,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        }]
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Please let me know when you are ready to begin, otherwise we can repeat these instructions before moving on."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "intro"
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The first SD we will present is the manding and motivation SD. This gives the child an opportunity to choose what they would like to work for and teach the learner to ask for what they want in a clear and concise manner. This interaction would go as follows."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "What do you want to work for?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "kid",

      "verbal": {
        "text": "... I want to work for the ball."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",

      "verbal": {
        "text": "Awesome! Let's work for the ball today!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Roll",
          "intensity": 0.3,
          "duration": 1.5,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "This demonstrates a proper response from the child. Clear and prompt speech with no problematic behavior. In that case, your job would be to reinforce the correct behavior as I demonstrated. Does this make sense before moving on? If not, please ask me to repeat this section."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "manding"
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next SD we will go through is the imitative SD. This SD focuses on teaching the learner to copy modeled actions, helping them build foundational skills in attending, motor imitation, and following demonstrated behavior. With these prompts, our goal is to show an action and have the learner reproduce it as accurately as possible. An example of this is as follows."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... Do this"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.5,
          "duration": 1.0,
          "repeats": 2,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "That's nodding your head! Good job nodding your head!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Does the interaction help make it clear the purpose and flow of this SD? We can either repeat this interaction or continue onto another SD. What would you like to do?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "receptive"
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next SD we will go through is the receptive SD. This builds listening and comprehension skills by teaching the learner how to respond appropriately when given directions. With these prompts, it is our job to teach the learner to understand and respond to spoken instruction. An example of this is as follows."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... Shake your head."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "GazeAway",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 2,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Let's try that again. Can you shake your head?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 2,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Nice job shaking your head! Thank you for letting me help you!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "As you can see, when the learner fails to respond to the prompt, it is our duty to re-prompt them by repeating the SD and giving them some kind of assistance. In this case, I shook my head to demonstrate to the learner what action they should complete."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },
      
    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Is it clear what you should do when the learner doesn't respond to our initial SD? If not, we can repeat this interaction to ensure your understanding. You will have to model these interactions yourself after, so your comprehension is important. What would you like to do?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "receptive_second"
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next SD we will go through is tacting. The purpose of this SD is to teach the learner how to label or describe things within their environment. In this SD, the learner should both name the correct item and respond spontaneously and with minimal prompting."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Now, what is in front of me?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Car"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.6,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Roll",
          "intensity": 0.5,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job, that is a car!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

     {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Is this clear? We want to ensure that the learner knows how to put words to what they see or experience. We can continue if you are ready, or shall I repeat?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "tacting"
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next and final SD we will go through in this phase is emotion labeling. The purpose here is to teach the learner to properly identify and name emotional states either in themselves or others. Here we want the learner to correctly identify the emotion presented as well as be able to map the facial expressions or context to emotion labels. Here is what this would look like."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Great job! I do feel happy right now!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "We have now succesfully introduced all of the SDs necessary for this study! If you would like me to repeat the emotion labeling SD I am happy to do so, otherwise let's cotninue onto the final stage of modeling. Which would you prefer?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "emotion"
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The final thing we will go over in this phase is how to properly perform error correction for an incorrect learner response. This is done to help the child learn how to properly respond following an error. Remember that we have previously covered what a correct resposne looks like."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },
    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Correct learner responses are characterized by both promptness and correctness. By enforcing correct responses be made, we are teaching that mistakes are corrected and not ignored. If the learner is able to succesfully answer our SD after re-prompting or modeling then we know we have done our job."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 0.5,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Remember error correction is performed as follows. Following the incorrect response, we will re-prompt the learner while giving some form of assistance, such as nodding your head while asking to nod head. After the child response, it is our job to reinforce if correct, and move into asking a high-probability SD. These will be predetermined and are based upon what the learner has already mastered."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "After asking these high-probability SDs and getting the learner response, their answer should be reinforced before we redeliver the initial SD. At this point, we go through the trial normally and reinforce a correct response or continue the cycle if incorrect. An example of this kind of correction is as follows."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "...angry."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Angry",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Not quite, let's try again. How do I feel? Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "VeryHappy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job I do feel happy! Now can you shake your head?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job shaking your head! How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job! I do feel happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "This is the end of the error correction practice and end of the modeling module. It is recommended to go through the error correction at least once more by asking me to repeat it; however, if you are ready to move onto the rehearsal stage then feel free to tell me so."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "error_correction"
    }
  ]
}